issue.body:
**Description**
Update SafeInt version.
Note that although the new version is not a release commit, it is one commit beyond the most recent release as of 04/27/2022 and the author said that the change in that commit is minor and didn't need a version number increase: https://github.com/dcleblanc/SafeInt/issues/37#issuecomment-897325710

**Motivation and Context**
Fix compiler warning (fix #11373).

body:
@skottmckay Thanks for finding the SafeInt issue.

> @edgchen1 Can we remove SafeInt.hpp from the pod? I didn't see any direct usage of SafeInt in the objective-c api. There's an include of SafeInt.hpp in ort_value.mm but no actual usage.

There is a usage of a SafeInt helper here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/88ff48910da946ebce8d695ea721e86ea9a13c7d/objectivec/src/ort_value.mm#L112

Trying to update ORT's SafeInt version: #11379

> Hope the pod can be fixed in the next release

Unfortunately, it did not make it in 1.11.1, but it should be in 1.12.

I am experiencing the same issue. Any potential workaround is difficult to implement in an automated manner, which is required for certain CI and release processes.

Will this be fixed in the 1.12 release or has this been undone by #11500?

> I am experiencing the same issue. Any potential workaround is difficult to implement in an automated manner, which is required for certain CI and release processes.
> 
> Will this be fixed in the 1.12 release or has this been undone by #11500?

It should be fixed in 1.12. The release branch has SafeInt at commit [ff15c6a](https://github.com/dcleblanc/SafeInt/tree/ff15c6ada150a5018c5ef2172401cb4529eac9c0).
